==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tragopan
<hw>Trag"o*pan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>tragopan</ets> a fabulous Ethiopian bird, Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species of Asiatic pheasants
of the genus <gen>Ceriornis</gen>. They are brilliantly colored with a
variety of tints, the back and breast are usually covered with white or
buff ocelli, and the head is ornamented with two bright-colored, fleshy
wattles. The crimson tragopan, or horned pheasant (<spn>Ceriornis
satyra</spn>), of India is one of the best-known species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tragus</ent>⟦br⟧
